Serialized Form

  • Package jMusicMetaManager

    • Class jMusicMetaManager.RecordingMetaData extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      42806L

      • Serialized Fields

        • file_path

          java.lang.String file_path
          The file path of the recording referred to.

        • title

          java.lang.String title
          The title of the recording.

        • artist

          java.lang.String artist
          The performer(s) of the recording.

        • composer

          java.lang.String composer
          The composer(s) of the recording.

        • album

          java.lang.String album
          The name of the album that the recording belongs to.

        • disc_number

          int disc_number
          The disc number of the album that the recording belongs to. Only relevant for multi-disc albums. Set to 1 by default if information is not specified.

        • discs_in_set

          int discs_in_set
          The total number of discs in a mult-disc album. Set to 1 by default if information is not specified.

        • track_number

          int track_number
          The track number of the recording on the album that it belongs to.

        • total_tracks

          int total_tracks
          The total number of tracks in the album that the recording belongs to.

        • compilation

          int compilation
          Whether or not the album is a compilation album. A value of +1 corresponds to true, 0 to false and -1 to unknown. If this is acquired from parsing the ID3 tags, of an MP3, it is set to true if the file path of the file includes the substring "Compilations".

        • year

          int year
          The year that the recording was recorded.

        • genres

          java.lang.String[] genres
          The genre(s) of the recording. The genres field of ID3 or iTunes XML is interpereted by assuming that any occurences of " + " are meant to separate multiple genre, and these are parsed into separate entries in the genres array.

        • duration

          long duration
          The length in seconds of the recording.

        • comments

          java.lang.String comments
          Any comments associated with the recording.

        • bit_rate

          int bit_rate
          The bit rate of the recording.

        • is_copy_protected

          int is_copy_protected
          Set to 1 if the recording is copy protected, 0 if it is not and -1 if this informatino is not known.

        • from_iTunes_XML

          boolean from_iTunes_XML
          True if metadata was acquired from iTunes XML.

        • from_id3

          boolean from_id3
          True if metadata was acquired from the ID3 tag of an MP3.

        • date_added

          java.util.Date date_added
          The date that the recording was added to the database. Set to the date when an object of this class is constructed by default, but is set to the date noted in an iTunes XML file if such information is available.

        • calculate_absolute_ED_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox calculate_absolute_ED_checkbox

        • absolute_ED_threshold_textfield

          javax.swing.JTextField absolute_ED_threshold_textfield
          The maximum absolute edit distance permissible for two strings to be considered likely to be identical. Related to the calculate_absolute_ED_checkbox field.

        • calculate_proportional_ED_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox calculate_proportional_ED_checkbox
          Whether or not the edit distance is calculated between pairs of differing values found for a field, and a threshold based on the absolute edit distance between each pair divided by the length of the longer field is used to determine if the values should likely in fact be the same.

        • proportional_ED_threshold_textfield

          javax.swing.JTextField proportional_ED_threshold_textfield
          The maximum proportional edit distance permissible for two strings to be considered likely to be identical (calculated by dividing the absolute distance by the length of the longer field). Related to the calculate_proportional_ED_checkbox field.

        • calculate_subset_ED_checkbox

          javax.swing.JCheckBox calculate_subset_ED_checkbox
          Whether or not the edit distance is calculated between pairs of differing values found for a field, and a threshold based on the absolute edit distance between each pair minus the difference in lengths of the fields, all divided by the length of the shorter field, is used to determine if the values should likely in fact be the same.

        • subset_ED_threshold_textfield

          javax.swing.JTextField subset_ED_threshold_textfield
          The maximum subset edit distance permissible for two strings to be considered likely to be identical (calculated by subtracting the difference in length from the absolute edit distance of the two strings and dividing the result by the length of the shorter field). Related to the calculate_proportional_ED_checkbox calculate_subset_ED_checkbox.

        • list_all_postmerge_metadata_checkbox

        • list_sorted_recording_metadata_checkbox

          Whether or not a report is generated alphabetically listing each genre present. All artists present that have at least one recording in a given genre are listed under that genre's entry as well as the number of recordings by the artist belonging to the given genre and the percentage of the recordings in that genre that they represent.

        • list_composers_by_genre

All composers present that have at least one recording in a given genre are listed under that genre's entry as well as the number of recordings by the composer belonging to the given genre and the percentage of the recordings in that genre that they represent.
